examples.en: Three diplomats were expelled for spying.
She was expelled from school for bad behavior.
He was expelled from his native country.
Students can be expelled for refusing to conform to school rules.
The family were so ashamed when the youngest son was expelled from his school.
Foreign priests were expelled from the country.
He was positively triumphant when the school troublemaker finally got expelled.
You are expelled from the house which you have indelibly disgraced.
Jews were expelled from Vienna, many to settle in the nearby hinterland.
The school condemns cheating, and any student caught cheating will be expelled.
He was expelled for making racist remarks.
The emperor ordained that all foreigners be expelled.
Two girls were expelled from school for taking drugs.
The main opposition leader was expelled from her party.
He refused to withdraw his remarks and was expelled from the Party.
